            "answer_text": "Let f(x) = x^3+13x^2+31x-45 be the given polynomial. Putting x=1 in f(x), we obtain f (1)=(1)^3+13(1)^2+31(1)-45 = 1+13+31\u201345 =45\u201345 =0 Therefore, (x-1) is a factor of f(x). Now, x^3+13x^2+31x-45 = x^2(x-1)+x^2+13x^2+31x-45 = x^2(x-1)+14x^2+31x-45 = x^2(x-1)+14x(x-1)+14x+31x-45 = x^2(x-1)+14x(x-1)+45x-45 = x^2(x-1)+14x(x-1)+45(x-1) = (x-1)(x^2+14x+45) =(x-1){x^2+5x+9x+45} =(x-1){x(x+5)+9(x+5)} =(x-1)(x+5)(x+9) Hence, x^3+13x^2+31x-45=(x-1)(x+5)(x+9) ",
